Troops of Operation Hadarin Daji have neutralized 11 bandits and rescued 18 captives in air and ground operations in Zamfar and Sokoto States. The Coordinator Defence Media Operation Major General John Enenche in a statement said the troops in a subsidiary operation code name Chingaba along Maru-Dansadau axis in Zamfara killed 9 bandits , rescued 18 kidnapped victims comprising 10 men, four women and Four minors. In a similar development, troops on 11 April 2020 following credible information conducted a sting operation at Isah Road close to Sarwa Village in Isah LGA Sokoto State and arrested a gun runner known as Alhaji. He said  at the point of collection, the gun runner’s men in ambush opened fire on troops leading his death. The Coordinator said the men fled with various degrees of gunshot wounds. However, the troops  recovered One GPMG PKT, 140 rounds of 12.7mm, 50 three blank ammunition and One motorcycle. He noted that on the same day,  troops of FOB Dangulbi and Dansadau at a blocking force at Gobirawa neutralised one bandit, recovered one AK 47 rifle, three 7.62mm special ammunition, water jet explosives, 2 inches Det 33 cable for IED and one motorcycle. General Enenche said the Village Head of Mutumji handed over one AK 47 rifle captured from bandits to troops at FOB Dansadau following sustained action on the bandits in Mutunj and Dansadau in Maru LGA on 10 April 2020, The Coordinator therefore solicited support from Nigerians by continuously providing information for the enhancement of troops operations.